t Places in Warangal Tourist Places in Digha Tourist Places in Erode Tourist Places in Sambalpur Tourist Places in Vietnam next ? ? prev Tourist Places in Kolhapur In southwest Maharashtra, Kolhapur is placed on the Panchaganga River. Kolhapur is 230 kilometres from Pune and has a long history connected to the Marathas. Kolhapur is famous for its necklaces and sandals, which are popular worldwide. Kolhasur, a demon destroyed by Goddess Mahalakshmi, is the mythological figure from whom Kolhapur derives its name. In honour of Goddess Mahalakshmi, the well-known Mahalakshmi temple is located here. The food, jewellery, and sandals of Kolhapur are famous throughout India. It is a place that welcomes tourists and with easily accessible to hotels and restaurants. Here refers to some of the best tourist places in Kolhapur, which tourists should never miss. 1. Shree Mahalaxmi Mandir The Shree Mahalaxmi Mandir, constructed in the seventh century under the time of the Chalukyas, is one of the most tranquil locations to visit in Kolhapur. It is a famous Hindu pilgrimage site where devotees from various areas travel to seek blessings. The Hindu religion honours Mahalakshmi, sometimes referred to as Goddess Ambabai. One of India's most significant pilgrimage sites is the temple, and the distance between the temple and the city's Central Bus Depot is roughly 5 kilometres. Location: Kolhapur, Maharashtra 416012, Mahadwar Road, B Ward, and C Ward Ideal Time: June through February Hours: 5:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m. and 4:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. 2. New Palace Understand Chatrapati Shahu Maharaj's way of life by visiting the New Palace, which was constructed on the Bhavani Mandap Kasaba Bawada Road. New Palace is one of the best tourist destinations in Kolhapur if you love history because it displays the ancient artefacts and valuables of the Maharaja and his family. The first floor has been converted into a museum, with the bottom floor remaining off-limits to visitors. The Palace is made of black polished stone and has an unusual architectural design. Best Period: June through February Time: 9:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Price: INR 18 per individual 3. Panhala Fort The Panhala Fort, the enormous Fort in the Deccan area, is placed close to Kolhapur City. The fact that it connects Maharashtra to the Arabian Sea via Bijapur fascinates anybody who enjoys learning about history and geography. The Indo-Islamic architecture adds to the Fort's presentation of numerous themes, bastions, and other artefacts from many royal families. The Maratha empire formerly developed here, and visitors can also get a bird's-eye view of the surrounding area from the top of the hill. Best Period: June through February Hours: Always open 4. Radhanagari Wildlife Sanctuary The Radhanagari Wildlife Sanctuary is a must-see attraction in Kolhapur since it is the ideal location for visitors. They may see different species of birds, reptiles, and several types of animals here. The Sanctuary is near Radhanagari, which is crossed by the Bhogavati, Dudhganga, Tulsi, Kalama, and Dirba rivers. This area is home to a unique variety of plants and wildlife, including sambar, gigantic squirrels, spotted deer, mouse deer, and sloth bears in large numbers. Best Time: June to September during the monsoon season. Time: 7:00 am to 2:30 pm The price per person begins at INR 120. 5. Shri Binkhambi Ganesh Mandir The Shri Binkhambi Ganesh Mandir, constructed to glorify Lord Ganesh, is one of Kolhapur's most peaceful tourist destinations. As the temple is formed out of a single pillar, the temple's architecture is highly intriguing, drawing visitors from all over the world. One of the top tourist attractions in Kolhapur is this location where visitors may worship Lord Ganesha for his blessing. Best Period: From June to February Time: Open from 5:30 a.m. to 8:00 p.m. 6. Kopeshwar Temple Kopeshwar Temple was erected on the banks of the river Krishna in the 12th century to receive Lord Shiva's blessings. The temple is elaborately constructed, and its beautiful pillars are decorated with representations of gods and goddesses. There are also idols of a few other gods, including Vishnu, the Nandi bull, and several others. Due to its outstanding construction, the temple draws not only worshippers but also history lovers. Best Period: Monsoon season, from June through September. Times are from 7:00 am to 11:30 am and from 4:00 pm to 8:00 pm. 7. Sagareshwar Deer Sanctuary The Sagareshwar Deer Sanctuary, a protected area in the Kolhapur district, is an additional attraction among the many sites to see in Kolhapur. This area has 11 square kilometres of artificial forest, and there is wildlife. Whether you're looking for an unusual variety of plants or animals, this is the ideal location. Best Period: June through February Time: 8:00 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. 8. Rankala Lake Rankala Lake, a well-known attraction in the area, is one of the many tourist destinations in Kolhapur. The lake, which combines Rajghat and Maraghat, was constructed by "Shri Chhatrapati Shahu Maharaj", the king of Kolhapur. It spreads across an area of 107 hectares, and the sights it offers are almost unimaginable. The lake is thought to have been constructed by the Maharaj and has a long history going back to ancient times. Rankala Lake is the ideal location for you if you're seeking a place to relax and calm your mind. Best Period: June through September Time: Always open 9. Jyotiba Temple One of the most stunning spots in Kolhapur is the "Jyotiba Temple," which is in the middle of the city. The temple is filled with gulal when gulal or rings are delivered to God as a sign of affection. Over 3124 feet above sea level, where the temple is located, you may gaze at the town's stunning view. The God named "Jyotiba", who resides in the temple is thought to be a combination of three divine gods. According to the locals, one should visit the temple after asking the Goddess "Mahalaxmi" for her blessing. Best Period: June through February Time: 6:00 a.m. to 10:30 p.m. 10. Siddhagiri Gramjivan Museum Kaneri's Siddhagiri Gramjivan Museum is the best option for visitors. It is also known as the Kaneri Math and contains a stunning Shiva temple inside the Shri Kshetra Siddhagiri Math. A visitor may see figures made of wax and cement at this museum that reflects a villager's way of life. Throughout its entire 7-acre area, the museum is encircled by beautiful nature on all sides. Best Period: June through February Time: 9:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. 11. Gaganbawada Gaganbawada, also known as the Sahyadris, is a town on the Western Ghats that is 55 kilometres from Kolhapur. The undeveloped hill village is known for its nearby attractions, including the Gagangad Fort, Bhuibavda Ghat, and Karul Ghat; the village is featured in several Bollywood films. Best times to go: August until April. 12. Ramtirth Waterfall Ramtirth waterfall, a natural waterfall famous for its incomparable tranquillity and stunning surroundings, flows down on the banks of the River Hiranyakeshi in Ajara Taluka, Kolhapur. The area is mainly visited for daytime picnics and to escape the city's noise. There are also several temples in the neighbourhood, which are always filled with visitors. 13. Dream World Water Park The Dream World Water Park is a great place to slide down into the water and play with the colourful water balloons. Up to 8 slides in various colours are available to play about in the water and enjoy yourself with your family. In addition, there is a dazzling deep pool and a shallow side of the pool where you may rest. Additionally, a cafe is constructed inside the park where you may enjoy delicious treats. Best Period: May through October Hours are 10:00 am to 9:00 pm. Price: INR 500 per person and above. 14. Kalamba Lake The Kalamba Lake covers 63 hectares and is one of the most impressive spots to see in Kolhapur. And this is the main water supply for the entire city. The lake's base is Katyayni hill, and the city is close to the lake's smooth water flow. During the winter, many migrating birds arrive at this lake, increasing its attractiveness. Best Period: June through September Hours: Always accessible 15. Shalini Palace One of the most popular attractions in Kolhapur is the Shalini Palace, built on Rankala Lake's shores. For Princess Shalini Raje, this luxurious Palace was constructed at the beginning of the 19th century. The architecture at the time explains the manufacturing cost, around INR 800,000. The Palace, which is a perfect place to relax, is surrounded by lovely gardens and pathways of palm trees. It is now a luxurious hotel and one of Kolhapur's Royal Palace. Best Period: June through February Time: 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. 16. Vishalgad Fort One of the most significant forts built by the Maratha kings was Vishalgad Fort, also known as "Khelna" locally. The Fort is located at a magnificent elevation of 3,500 feet above sea level, and the sights it offers will melt your heart. The Fort's name, Vishal, which means excellent, seems appropriate. Chhatrapati Shivaji constructed the Fort in 1058, and after he died, the Deccan kings took control of it. The Fort then returned to the Maratha empire. It is perfectly blended with nature and history, with beautiful green surroundings enclosing it from all sides. Best Period: June through February Time: 5:30 am to 8:00 pm are the times. 17. Chinmaya Ganadhish The highest statue of the Hindu God Ganesh in the entire world is called Chinmaya Ganadhish, and it is situated on the Pune-Bangalore Highway in Maharashtra, 14 kilometres from Kolhapur. A 24-foot-long foundation supports the statue's 61-foot height, which is its full height. 2001 saw its official opening. 18. Bhavani Mandap The Bhavani Mandap, also regarded as the oldest and most prominent structure in Kolhapur, formerly served as Chhatrapati Maharaj's royal court and Palace. The building is one of the city's most significant heritage structures and has been converted into a public monument. Inside the Palace can find Many statues, stuffed animals, wooden crowns, and Shahu Maharaj's sculptures. The Palace is one of the country's oldest examples of Indian architecture and is a wonder to see because it was constructed entirely of black stone. Best Period: October through February Time: from 6 am to 11 pm. 19. Dyp City Mall One of the best malls in the area is the DYP City Mall, located on Kolhapur-Pune Road. This mall features a variety of retail establishments, allowing you to shop for everything from budget-friendly to premium goods. Aside from this, here are a few shops where you may shop for clothing, accessories, jewellery, toys, and a vast array of other items. In addition, it is also surrounded by several restaurants where you may experience a variety of food. Hours: from 11:00 am till 11:00 pm. 20. Temlabai Mandir The Temlabai Hill and the Temlabai Temple take their names from the Goddess Temlabai. Temlabai is stated to have battled with Mahalakshmi to remove all evils, but after the war, Mahalakshmi did not give her the honour she deserved. Temlabai departed and stayed in the hills. The occasion from the Mahalakshmi temple to the Temlabai temple during the festival of Navratri is said to be the only occasion when Mahalakshmi and Temlabai would ever meet. 21. Radhanagari Dam The oldest dam in India is located at Radhanagari, close to Kolhapur, and was constructed on the Bhogawati River. The water from the dam is used in numerous neighbouring areas for agriculture and producing electricity. Furthermore, the dam is a well-liked tourist destination in the area due to its picturesque location. Way To Reach Kolhapur By Air Kolhapur is 250 kilometres away from Lohegaon Airport, which is reachable by buses and taxis that are accessible nearby. It takes around 4 hours and 15 minutes to drive to Kolhapur. The Chhatrapati Shivaji Airport in Mumbai is approximately 380 KM from Kolhapur, and the drive takes six and a half hours. Kolhapur is also constructing a new, smaller airport, but regular flights have not yet started. By train Miraj junction, placed at the station's endpoint and 50 kilometres from Kolhapur, is nearby. Trains from Kolhapur run to Mumbai, Delhi, and Nagpur on the north side. Trains to Solapur and Hyderabad are available on the east side, and Train connections to Tirupati and Banglore are in the south. By Road Kolhapur has an active bus station. The primary bus service provided by MSRTC (Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation) runs frequently and regularly from Kolhapur to Mumbai and Pune in the north. Solapur has connection toward East Sangali. Banglore connectivity is present in South Belgaum, and there is connectivity between Ratnagiri and Sindhudurg in the west. Next TopicTourist Places in Nashik ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions Trending Technologies Artificial Intelligence AWS Selenium Cloud Computing Hadoop ReactJS Data Science Angular 7 Blockchain Git Machine Learning DevOps B.Tech / MCA DBMS Data Structures DAA Operating System Computer Network Compiler Design Computer Organization Discrete Mathematics Ethical Hacking Computer Graphics Software Engineering Web Technology Cyber Security Automata C Programming C++ Java .Net Python Programs Control System Data Mining Data Warehouse Javatpoint Services JavaTpoint offers too many high quality services. Mail us on [email protected], to get more information about given services. Website Designing Website Development Java Development PHP Development WordPress Graphic Designing Logo Digital Marketing On Page and Off Page SEO PPC Content Development Corpor